external_knowledge:
- 'Seeds of simplicity' metaphorically refer to functions with 'simple' complexity;
- 'Sprouted and grown quickly enough to thrive' implies functions meeting the average execution time condition;
- 'Reach their bloom within a mere 10 seconds' indicates the average execution time being 10.0 or less.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS simple_function_count
FROM functions
WHERE complexity = 'simple';

